Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph list

list

Purpose:
  Enumerate Wiki Graph objects from a located Wiki Graph URI.

Use when:
  - You need objects of a kind without a text query, such as all chapters or all entities.

Usage:
  wikigraph <located-wkg-uri>/<chapter|entity|triple|source|summary|chunk> list [--limit <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]

Returns:
  - URI-addressable objects in document order.

Notes:
  - Conceptually, `list` is `search` without query text, scoped by a URI lens.
  - Use `<located-wkg-uri>/chapter`, `<located-wkg-uri>/entity`, `<located-wkg-uri>/triple`, `<located-wkg-uri>/source`, `<located-wkg-uri>/summary`, or `<located-wkg-uri>/chunk` to choose the collection.
  - Use `_` as an any-value placeholder in triple pattern lenses such as `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/Q2`.
  - Trailing triple placeholders may be omitted: `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1` means `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/_`.
  - Put the lens after a chapter URI, such as `<chapter-uri>/entity`, to list within one chapter.
  - Use `search` when you have query text.
  - Add `--evidence` or `--evidence <n>` to include source evidence previews on entity and triple results.
  - Add `--backlinks` to include reverse references on top-level source results; nested evidence sources are not expanded.
  - Use `wikigraph next <cursor>` for any returned `nextCursor`.
  - Use `wikigraph help uri` before constructing Wiki Graph URIs; bare filesystem paths are not valid object command inputs.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/chapter list
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/chapter/3/entity list --json
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/triple/_/_/Q178561 list
